ts and Paladin, SoL AA skill)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> =  Faster than Chain - almost as fast as Maximum bard speed.<br><br>*** What effect does color have on the horse?  <br>Tan and Brown horse are slightly cheaper (couple K) than White/Black horses.  No one has been able to come up with any functional difference - it's just appearance.<br><br>*** Do all the horse types look the same? <br>Aka is a rope pony the same looking as a chain Pony?  They do all look the same - although it would have be neat to see chain drapped over the horse. <br><br>*** Can you FD while riding a horse?  <br>Mixed answer - you CAN FD while riding a horse - but you drop 4-8 feet to the ground and occasionally take damage - which causes the mob to notice you again.  So it's best to  click off the horse before FDing - especially since the horse poofs when you FD anyway.  Whether or not you take damage when FDing on a horse - has to do with the angle of the ground you're FDing onto - aka... if you FD on a hill you're more likely to take some damage and break FD.<br><br>Other Horse info:<br>*Meditating is currently in effect while riding (makes sense to me) - no more standing/sitting/standing/sitting for casters.<br>**<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>          (new 1/8/02)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->** Medding while in COMBAT was removed in the 1/8/02 patch.  However, casters are still able to sit still on their horse and med.  It's not clear yet if medding is in effect while riding (moving).<br>*Charisma has a very large effect on horse price - 120's is enough to get to max price.  I posted the cheapest prices above.  (people paying 117 k pp for a horse are too lazy to get some charisma gear/buffs).<br>*Horses come with the added benefit of avoiding &quot;falling damage&quot; when running through a zone - apparently from a Safe Fall skill.<br>*Weight restrictions do not affect run speed while riding a horse (can run with lots of PP - not that you'd have much after buying a nice horse).<br>*Can't bash or bandage while riding a horse, but you can Kick.  Manuvering to melee (slow twisting) can be slow as there is a 1-2 second delay before the horse gets moving (need larger spurs).<br>*Bouncing on a horse can be visually (vestibularly) annoying - use F9 to avoid.  Also running while invis, negates this (without See Invis up obviously).<br>*You can cast spells while riding a horse - including Invis (the horse becomes Invis also).  Invis potions don't seem to work, but invis items (Circlet of Shadow) do.  (See below buggs).<br>*Horses stay with you when you zone from an outdoor to outdoor zone, but they poof when you zone into an indoor zone.<br>*Enchanters can use their illusions to get different types of horses (aka HIE Enc use gnome illusion - and then summon Horse and get pony).  But you have to cast the illusion before summoning the horse (or the horse disappears).  On a related issue - you also can summon pets and Familiars while on horseback.<br>*You do not suffer from Knockback spells while riding a horse - but you can still be stunned.  (<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      NEW 1/23/02</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This feature was removed from horses on 1/23/02 patch.)<br>*(<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      NEW 1/23/02 patch</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  You can now sell back your horse for a small price hit.  Perhaps people could post trade-in prices below, and I'll add it to this post.  There are 4 traders in the stables of the Bazaar - each of which will trade in, but only for 1 particular color.<br>*<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      New 1/23/02</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Levitate should now work on horses - although SoE doesn't seem to.  It may be hard for them to fix SoE since it has the levitate and SoW component together.<br><br>BUGS:<br>1) Following crash to desktop bug was fixed with 1/23/02 patch.<br>2) (<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Updated 1/17/02</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->)  Invis is DEFINITELY bugged when riding horses - whereas you character appears invis on your screen and the character con's indiff - some mobs will still agro you.  For example, Bats and Wolves - althought they con indiff in ME, will still attack you.  Not clear what is bugged - but perhaps the horse is incompletely invised.  In addition when you're &quot;invisible&quot;, part of your body can be seen moving back and forth while riding (while in first person view) - this is another possibility (incomplete invis while on horse-back).<br>3)  Can't cast Boon of Garou and many other buffs on OTHERS while riding a horse (it says that YOU can't change while riding a horse - even though you're casting it on someone else).  In addition - people may get the error message that you're OOR when trying to cast beneficial spells on you - even though they're standing right next to you.<br>4)  Your horse con's threateningly to you, when you're invis.  Usually cons ambiably.<br>5)  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (new)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->You can't interrupt a spell you start casting without moving (aka no duck) - this is being looked into according to Absor (Alan).<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NEW</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>STARTING and STOPPING (Giddy-Up Horsie) info:<br>Each time you summon your horse, you summon one that can start/stop faster or slower.  Similar to when a magician summons a pet - he gets a random (with in 5 levels) level pet.  So each time you summon a horse - you may notice it starting and stopping faster or slower than previously.  This gets a little complicated, because apparently having other movement speed buffs on you change the start/stop speed of your horse.  AKA having JBoots up when you summon your horse, seems to make it start/stop generally slower.  Don't know if SoW/SoE has an effect on start/stop speed yet, but I'll try to keep you updated.<br><br>COMPLETE AND UTTER RUMOR:<br>Horses may become Soulbound.<br><br>Maker, Enchanter 60<br>Sumin, Magician 60<br>Thumpie, Ogre SK 54<br>Druzz